{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, it is inherently interpretable because every verified LLM output can be traced back to an example from the ground truth knowledge graph.",
    "The algorithm (Fig. 5) begins by extracting medical phrases from language model outputs using named entity recognition (NER).",
    "The extracted phrases are cross-referenced to a biomedical knowledge graph for verification.",
    "If a phrase cannot be matched to the graph, it is deemed potential misinformation.",
    "Any LLM-generated passage containing at least one rejected medical phrase is marked for review."
  ]
}